questions.question:
Consider the following code snippet:

int arr[] = {5, 10, 15, 20, 25};
int *ptr = arr + 2;
cout << *ptr << ' ' << *(ptr - 1) << ' ' << *(ptr + 3) << endl;
cout << *ptr++ << ' ' << *ptr << endl;

a) What is the output of the first cout statement? (2 marks)
b) Explain how pointer arithmetic yields the values shown in part (a). (4 marks)
c) In the second cout statement, the expression *ptr++ is used. Using operator precedence, show exactly how this expression is evaluated, what value is printed, and the final value of ptr after the statement. (4 marks)
